CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1959, pg. 1, reads: "Please Help Them - Mr. and Mrs. Robert Tyler and their six children, who are being forced to move from a tinder-box house at 2817 Berthoud St., are in extreme mental anguish this week because they have no place to move. Can you help them? - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Tyler family, including Robert Tyler, Mrs. Tyler wearing short sleeved floral dress with rounded collar, and their six children, including girl wearing gingham skirt seated on tricycle, gathered on porch of house with wood clapboard siding, 2817 Berthoud Street, Hill District, another version
